1
00:00:01,869 --> 00:00:05,473
Killua: Nanika, will you...

2
00:00:05,539 --> 00:00:07,775
Please forgive me for being...

3
00:00:09,376 --> 00:00:11,278
Such a bad big brother?

4
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:13,647
Nanika: Okay.

5
00:00:17,751 --> 00:00:20,320
( Sighs )

6
00:00:20,387 --> 00:00:21,822
I...

7
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:23,991
Love you, killua.

8
00:00:24,057 --> 00:00:25,458
Gon: Mm-hmm.

9
00:00:25,526 --> 00:00:27,595
Ging: Don’t make
the same mistake again.

10
00:00:27,661 --> 00:00:29,763
And if there’s anyone
you should apologize to,

11
00:00:29,830 --> 00:00:31,598
it’s kite, not me.

12
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:35,002
from what you said,
i’m not sure he’s dead yet.

13
00:00:35,068 --> 00:00:37,304
Just go! Apologize!

14
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:39,707
( Gon sighing )

15
00:00:39,773 --> 00:00:42,509
Ging: But friends
apologize differently.

16
00:00:42,576 --> 00:00:43,944
Do you know how?

17
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:46,714
( Gon gasps )
Mm-mmm. Tell me.

18
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:49,016
ging: You have
to make them a promise.

19
00:00:49,082 --> 00:00:50,750
tell them
what you’ll do next time,

20
00:00:50,817 --> 00:00:53,720
and then you keep
that promise, no matter what.

21
00:00:53,787 --> 00:00:55,656
( Gon sighs )

22
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:57,257
( Grunts )

23
00:00:57,324 --> 00:00:58,492
♪

24
00:00:58,559 --> 00:01:00,428
( Singing in Japanese )

25
00:01:26,787 --> 00:01:30,958
♪ You can smile again

26
00:01:31,024 --> 00:01:33,226
( singing in Japanese )

27
00:01:33,293 --> 00:01:36,897
♪ You can fly away

28
00:01:36,964 --> 00:01:38,899
( singing in Japanese )

29
00:01:42,402 --> 00:01:44,337
♪

30
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:09,362
Koala: That girl was a redhead
just like you, actually.

31
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:14,401
♪

32
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:27,781
I shot her.

33
00:02:29,783 --> 00:02:33,320
But I wouldn’t have done it
if I didn’t have a good reason.

34
00:02:33,387 --> 00:02:36,590
you see, I knew
that the trash pursuing her

35
00:02:36,657 --> 00:02:38,792
would have tortured her alive.

36
00:02:38,859 --> 00:02:42,529
After my rebirth as an ant,
I had an epiphany.

37
00:02:42,596 --> 00:02:44,331
I realized that I was doing

38
00:02:44,398 --> 00:02:47,902
the exact same things
i’d done before.

39
00:02:55,442 --> 00:02:58,545
Before I was reborn,
i had a job,

40
00:02:58,612 --> 00:02:59,947
getting rid of people.

41
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:01,515
♪

42
00:03:01,582 --> 00:03:04,718
I’d get my orders,
and i’d pull the trigger.

43
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:07,187
What little time
I had to myself,

44
00:03:07,254 --> 00:03:08,956
I spent yelling at people.

45
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:13,660
It was a job anyone could do...

46
00:03:15,629 --> 00:03:19,666
A stupid cycle that continues,
even after rebirth.

47
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:20,667
( Projectile pops )

48
00:03:22,769 --> 00:03:24,804
I just wanted...

49
00:03:24,872 --> 00:03:29,276
To give her an escape
from the endless cycle.

50
00:03:29,343 --> 00:03:32,713
I’m not exactly sure
how it worked, but...

51
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:36,883
I thought if I let them
take her, torture her,

52
00:03:36,950 --> 00:03:38,718
and then finish her off,

53
00:03:38,785 --> 00:03:41,921
the cycle would repeat itself.

54
00:03:45,959 --> 00:03:48,929
Imagine a dull, simple life
in the middle of nowhere,

55
00:03:48,996 --> 00:03:52,366
where one lived
in peace and quiet

56
00:03:52,432 --> 00:03:57,938
until suddenly assaulted
by mindless violence and killed.

57
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:04,812
As I shot her, I prayed
she would escape that cycle.

58
00:04:04,878 --> 00:04:06,313
( Projectile pops )

59
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,652
But it didn’t matter
at all what I did.

60
00:04:11,718 --> 00:04:14,955
The queen still ate
hundreds of humans.

61
00:04:15,022 --> 00:04:16,757
And, when they were reborn,

62
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:20,460
only a precious few could
remember their prior lives.

63
00:04:20,527 --> 00:04:23,597
but I suppose
it just might be possible

64
00:04:23,664 --> 00:04:27,301
that most of the human souls
managed to escape safely.

65
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:30,303
But I wanted to do something.

66
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:33,840
i wanted to feel like
I was helping them to escape.

67
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:39,913
But if you’re inside that body,
then of course she isn’t.

68
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:43,617
it must mean
that she somehow escaped.

69
00:04:43,684 --> 00:04:47,655
And, though I keep looking,
I have yet to run into an ant

70
00:04:47,721 --> 00:04:51,325
who’s told me that I killed them
before our transition.

71
00:04:51,391 --> 00:04:55,495
I wonder, did they all escape?

72
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:59,466
Before all this happened,

73
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:02,169
I didn’t believe
that souls existed.

74
00:05:02,236 --> 00:05:06,674
I didn’t think humans were worth
any more than flies or fleas.

75
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:09,443
They lived, they died...

76
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:13,880
And that the ego was
nothing more than a glitch,

77
00:05:13,947 --> 00:05:16,383
a side effect
because the human brain

78
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,218
was a complex thing.

79
00:05:18,285 --> 00:05:20,220
( Chorus vocalizing )

80
00:05:21,889 --> 00:05:24,792
You die, and it’s over,

81
00:05:24,858 --> 00:05:27,494
dust to dust,
scattered to the wind.

82
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:33,266
I believed those tiny fragments
served no purpose whatsoever.

83
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,268
( Bubbling )

84
00:05:37,771 --> 00:05:40,774
And yet here I am,
repeating the cycle

85
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:43,477
over and over again.

86
00:05:44,745 --> 00:05:47,615
Although I look
totally different now,

87
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:50,884
i’m still doing the same
stupid things i’ve always done.

88
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,922
It made me think.

89
00:05:54,988 --> 00:05:59,726
I may be stupid, but I
can’t deny the things I know,

90
00:05:59,793 --> 00:06:02,162
and I won’t ignore
what I don’t know.

91
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,268
I died,

92
00:06:07,334 --> 00:06:12,206
and my body was torn up
and digested into molecules.

93
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:15,342
But it didn’t end there.

94
00:06:17,945 --> 00:06:20,714
I always figured being reduced
to something that small

95
00:06:20,781 --> 00:06:22,883
would be the end, but this stuff

96
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:26,220
possessed a power
I could never have imagined.

97
00:06:30,424 --> 00:06:34,895
Particles no larger than pollen,
almost too small to see,

98
00:06:34,962 --> 00:06:37,498
have enough energy
to impact our health,

99
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,266
and not just now,

100
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:43,437
tens or even hundreds
of millions of years later.

101
00:06:44,705 --> 00:06:47,541
and our DNA,
which is even smaller,

102
00:06:47,608 --> 00:06:50,878
contains all of the information
that comprises us

103
00:06:50,944 --> 00:06:53,780
within an elegant double helix.

104
00:06:54,948 --> 00:06:56,817
It seems small things,

105
00:06:56,884 --> 00:06:59,387
infinitesimally small things,

106
00:06:59,453 --> 00:07:00,688
aren’t meaningless.

107
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:02,189
They’re needed to build

108
00:07:02,256 --> 00:07:04,892
the enormous space
known as the universe.

109
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:07,928
Just because something is small,

110
00:07:07,995 --> 00:07:10,798
doesn’t mean
it produces any less energy,

111
00:07:10,864 --> 00:07:12,532
not by a long shot.

112
00:07:14,868 --> 00:07:17,170
the soul
is probably pretty small,

113
00:07:17,237 --> 00:07:21,241
but it still contains enough
energy to reincarnate itself.

114
00:07:21,308 --> 00:07:25,479
Does that mean I was reborn
to repeat that cycle?

115
00:07:25,546 --> 00:07:29,250
The truth is, I don’t know
what the future holds.

116
00:07:29,316 --> 00:07:34,755
Understand this is nothing more
than speculation on my part,

117
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:36,222
but something inside me

118
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,893
is saying I need
to stop repeating myself.

119
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,495
If I had to guess,

120
00:07:41,562 --> 00:07:44,665
i’d say i’m forced
to live this over and over

121
00:07:44,731 --> 00:07:46,266
because there was something

122
00:07:46,333 --> 00:07:49,736
I failed to feed my heart
the first time around.

123
00:07:54,575 --> 00:07:57,411
Have you ever noticed
that the body moves slower

124
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,612
if the heart’s not into it?

125
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,815
With me, I just keep thinking

126
00:08:01,882 --> 00:08:05,819
that I can’t let things
stay this way anymore.

127
00:08:05,886 --> 00:08:09,423
I know it isn’t right.

128
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:11,591
I’ll repeat the cycle,

129
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:13,760
and, once again,
i’ll keep thinking

130
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:15,929
about how
I have to change things...

131
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:18,365
♪

132
00:08:18,432 --> 00:08:20,868
Because I always made
the wrong choice.

133
00:08:22,002 --> 00:08:23,637
I shouldn’t have shot that girl.

134
00:08:23,704 --> 00:08:26,640
It should have shot
the ones chasing her.

135
00:08:26,707 --> 00:08:28,576
that’s who
I should have focused on.

136
00:08:32,412 --> 00:08:34,347
It’s no big deal, really.

137
00:08:34,414 --> 00:08:37,717
it just means I was
the biggest scumbag of all.

138
00:08:37,784 --> 00:08:40,854
The price for cleansing
a tainted soul was too heavy.

139
00:08:40,921 --> 00:08:43,657
I avoided atoning for my sins...

140
00:08:44,725 --> 00:08:46,527
Because it was too painful.

141
00:08:47,594 --> 00:08:48,728
While selfishly praying

142
00:08:48,795 --> 00:08:51,464
that her soul
would escape and be free,

143
00:08:51,532 --> 00:08:53,801
I was desperate
to avoid getting hurt.

144
00:08:55,269 --> 00:08:58,639
I shot her to protect myself.

145
00:09:02,509 --> 00:09:05,812
And now i’m trying
to save myself yet again

146
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:10,484
by confessing my sins to you,
just because you look like her.

147
00:09:12,286 --> 00:09:13,821
( Sighs )

148
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:15,522
Seriously...

149
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,759
I’m hopeless, aren’t I?

150
00:09:19,826 --> 00:09:22,796
Still, thanks for listening.

151
00:09:24,598 --> 00:09:25,866
Kite: Wait a minute.

152
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:27,201
Don’t run away.

153
00:09:31,305 --> 00:09:33,407
You should just stay with me.

154
00:09:35,509 --> 00:09:37,945
Forever, actually.

155
00:09:38,011 --> 00:09:40,647
You’ll stay by me,
the one you shot,

156
00:09:40,714 --> 00:09:43,951
and you’ll live a life
you believe is right.

157
00:09:45,319 --> 00:09:47,755
And that’s an order, by the way.

158
00:09:47,821 --> 00:09:49,656
You don’t have any choice
in the matter.

159
00:09:49,723 --> 00:09:52,259
You may want to press
the reset button,

160
00:09:52,326 --> 00:09:54,261
but you won’t be allowed.

161
00:09:54,328 --> 00:09:58,265
Every day of your life,
you’ll spend apologizing,

162
00:09:58,332 --> 00:10:00,334
and you’ll work.

163
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,702
I’ll work you so hard
that you’ll never have time

164
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:05,672
to sit and worry
about what’s right or wrong.

165
00:10:05,739 --> 00:10:09,409
And you will apologize to me.
You’ll do as I say

166
00:10:09,476 --> 00:10:12,846
and live for me
to make up for what you’ve done.

167
00:10:16,650 --> 00:10:19,219
if you lose
even a little of this resolve

168
00:10:19,286 --> 00:10:22,322
and start backsliding,
i’ll kill you.

169
00:10:26,026 --> 00:10:28,729
You can live in peace
knowing that.

170
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:37,437
Spin: Hey, kite,
you got a visitor.

171
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:39,673
Kite: Let ’em in.

172
00:10:51,518 --> 00:10:53,353
♪

173
00:11:05,132 --> 00:11:06,900
Gon: Kite?

174
00:11:06,967 --> 00:11:08,669
Kite: Yeah.

175
00:11:08,735 --> 00:11:09,803
( Gon gasps )

176
00:11:10,871 --> 00:11:11,839
I’m sorry.

177
00:11:14,741 --> 00:11:17,043
Kite: Come. Sit.

178
00:11:31,158 --> 00:11:32,092
( Gon groans )

179
00:11:32,159 --> 00:11:33,260
Kite: Sorry for what?

180
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:50,877
Gon: I left you
to fight all alone.

181
00:11:54,181 --> 00:11:57,117
I was too weak.

182
00:12:01,822 --> 00:12:05,626
but, next time,
I swear i’m gonna protect you!

183
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:13,334
Kite: I heard that you did
some really crazy stuff

184
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,168
in order to defeat pitou.

185
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:17,838
Gon: Yeah. I almost died.

186
00:12:19,106 --> 00:12:20,741
Kite: That doesn’t
change the fact

187
00:12:20,807 --> 00:12:24,678
that you defeated an enemy
who was far too much for me.

188
00:12:24,745 --> 00:12:27,948
Guess that means
I was right about you,

189
00:12:28,015 --> 00:12:29,884
so that’s something, I suppose.

190
00:12:31,151 --> 00:12:34,821
Gon: Without killua
and everybody else,

191
00:12:34,888 --> 00:12:36,790
I wouldn’t be here right now.

192
00:12:37,858 --> 00:12:39,093
I didn’t do it by myself.

193
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:40,661
I had their help.

194
00:12:45,032 --> 00:12:48,102
Kite: It seems that we both
needed more training.

195
00:12:49,169 --> 00:12:51,271
♪

196
00:12:59,379 --> 00:13:01,581
I hear you met Mr. Ging.

197
00:13:01,648 --> 00:13:03,750
( Gon gasps )
Did you talk to him?

198
00:13:03,817 --> 00:13:04,818
Kite: Yeah.

199
00:13:07,921 --> 00:13:10,257
And you should go back to him.

200
00:13:10,324 --> 00:13:12,259
( Gon sighs )

201
00:13:12,326 --> 00:13:15,629
kite: I know
what you wanted to say,

202
00:13:15,696 --> 00:13:18,032
and i’m really glad
you came to see me.

203
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:22,869
If I need help, I promise
that i’ll let you know.

204
00:13:22,936 --> 00:13:25,839
Tell killua I said hello.

205
00:13:28,942 --> 00:13:31,778
You’re a part of the gang now,

206
00:13:31,845 --> 00:13:36,049
and what you should do
is go back to Mr. Ging again.

207
00:13:38,018 --> 00:13:39,686
Gon: Okay.

208
00:13:39,753 --> 00:13:41,688
♪

209
00:13:59,706 --> 00:14:00,974
Koala: I’m sorry.

210
00:14:02,109 --> 00:14:03,877
Kite: You’re sorry?

211
00:14:03,944 --> 00:14:07,614
Koala: For trying to run away,
taking the easy way out.

212
00:14:09,883 --> 00:14:11,752
I’ll endure the suffering.

213
00:14:11,818 --> 00:14:13,987
That way, when I die,

214
00:14:14,054 --> 00:14:16,290
i’ll know
I did the best I could.

215
00:14:28,335 --> 00:14:29,636
Gon: Ging!

216
00:14:44,418 --> 00:14:47,087
Beans: I did my best
to stop him.

217
00:14:47,154 --> 00:14:49,089
Gon: That’s okay.

218
00:14:49,156 --> 00:14:52,292
I guess he didn’t say
he’d wait for me here.

219
00:14:52,359 --> 00:14:55,095
( Echoing )
...Here. ...Here. ...Here.

220
00:14:55,162 --> 00:14:57,097
♪

221
00:15:22,322 --> 00:15:24,257
( Wind gusting )

222
00:15:38,739 --> 00:15:41,675
Killua: Whoa. It’s huge!

223
00:15:41,742 --> 00:15:43,644
This is it,

224
00:15:43,710 --> 00:15:45,645
the tallest tree in the world!

225
00:15:53,187 --> 00:15:56,691
Man: The world tree stands
in the very center of the city.

226
00:15:56,757 --> 00:16:01,629
It measures in at an impressive
height of 1,784 meters.

227
00:16:01,695 --> 00:16:03,931
In fact, that gives it

228
00:16:03,997 --> 00:16:06,166
the unique distinction
of being taller

229
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:09,036
than any man-made structure
on the planet.

230
00:16:09,102 --> 00:16:11,338
Climbing the tree
isn’t forbidden, per se,

231
00:16:12,906 --> 00:16:15,175
but you do have to pay a fee,

232
00:16:15,242 --> 00:16:18,045
as well as sign
a written agreement.

233
00:16:18,111 --> 00:16:21,214
it’s easy enough
to reach the 500-meter point

234
00:16:21,281 --> 00:16:23,784
by stairs or even the elevator,

235
00:16:23,851 --> 00:16:26,654
but, beyond that,
you’ll be risking your life.

236
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:30,657
and, every year, around
3,000 people attempt the climb,

237
00:16:30,724 --> 00:16:34,261
but roughly 94% of them fail
to reach the 1,000-meter point

238
00:16:34,328 --> 00:16:37,264
and are forced
to turn back in shame.

239
00:16:37,331 --> 00:16:40,267
There’s another 4%
who are forced to pay

240
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:43,671
an extremely pricey fee
to be rescued from the branches.

241
00:16:43,737 --> 00:16:47,274
still, that’s better
than the 1% who fall and die.

242
00:16:47,341 --> 00:16:51,078
That means that, every year,
there are only about 30 people

243
00:16:51,144 --> 00:16:53,880
who are able to make it
to the top of the world tree,

244
00:16:53,947 --> 00:16:57,250
then come back down without
sustaining bodily injury.

245
00:16:58,952 --> 00:17:01,188
( Footsteps tapping )

246
00:17:03,824 --> 00:17:04,992
Killua: So...

247
00:17:07,694 --> 00:17:10,163
This is as far as we’re going.

248
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,164
Gon: Right.

249
00:17:11,231 --> 00:17:12,833
Killua: So be careful, okay?

250
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,068
Gon: Mm-hmm.

251
00:17:16,637 --> 00:17:19,840
Killua, thanks a whole lot
for everything!

252
00:17:20,908 --> 00:17:21,842
Killua: Sure!

253
00:17:21,909 --> 00:17:24,111
Well, the truth is,

254
00:17:24,178 --> 00:17:27,248
after you told me you
were gonna defeat pitou alone,

255
00:17:27,314 --> 00:17:30,150
not to mention that it
was none of my business,

256
00:17:30,217 --> 00:17:34,054
I got pretty depressed.

257
00:17:34,121 --> 00:17:35,756
( Gon groans )

258
00:17:35,822 --> 00:17:38,258
I’m really sorry.

259
00:17:38,325 --> 00:17:39,593
Alluka: Big brother!

260
00:17:39,660 --> 00:17:40,861
( Killua chuckles )

261
00:17:40,928 --> 00:17:44,832
Well, you already apologized,

262
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:47,234
and I think I can say
i’m only with alluka now

263
00:17:47,301 --> 00:17:49,103
because of the time
I spent with you.

264
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:51,872
Oh, by the way,

265
00:17:51,939 --> 00:17:53,674
she’s the one who healed you.

266
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:55,675
Gon: Huh?! Is that true?!

267
00:17:55,742 --> 00:17:58,745
why are you
just telling me that now?!

268
00:17:58,812 --> 00:18:02,316
It really would have helped if I
had known that a lot sooner!

269
00:18:02,382 --> 00:18:03,717
( Groaning )

270
00:18:03,784 --> 00:18:05,219
Killua: Sorry.

271
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:08,688
We don’t want too many people
knowing about this.

272
00:18:08,755 --> 00:18:11,858
It’s sort of a complicated
family thing, you know?

273
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:13,727
- ( Gon yelps )
- Killua: Let’s go over here!

274
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:19,166
Can you tell nanika
to come out, alluka?

275
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:21,335
- Alluka: Yeah.
- ( Nen whooshes )

276
00:18:23,704 --> 00:18:25,206
Gon: Oh!

277
00:18:25,272 --> 00:18:27,040
♪

278
00:18:27,107 --> 00:18:28,942
Killua: So now you know.

279
00:18:29,009 --> 00:18:31,812
she has the power
to Grant any wish that I make.

280
00:18:32,913 --> 00:18:34,348
Gon: Any wish?

281
00:18:34,414 --> 00:18:36,016
Killua: She was
locked in our house

282
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:37,685
for a real long time

283
00:18:37,751 --> 00:18:39,853
for the crime
of being too awesome.

284
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:42,256
But she’s out,
because you gave me

285
00:18:42,322 --> 00:18:44,858
the opportunity
to help get her out.

286
00:18:44,925 --> 00:18:49,263
And now i’m going to protect her
for the rest of my life.

287
00:18:53,901 --> 00:18:56,337
To be honest, we owe you one.

288
00:18:56,403 --> 00:18:57,905
Thanks for everything.

289
00:18:57,971 --> 00:18:59,072
Nanika: ’kay.

290
00:18:59,139 --> 00:19:00,807
Gon: No! No way!

291
00:19:00,874 --> 00:19:04,778
You’ve got it wrong.
I should be thanking you.

292
00:19:16,223 --> 00:19:17,791
No good.

293
00:19:17,858 --> 00:19:19,593
If we stay much longer...

294
00:19:21,195 --> 00:19:22,596
Killua: You’re right.

295
00:19:27,701 --> 00:19:29,102
( Overlapping chatter )

296
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:31,905
I’ll be traveling to all kinds
of places with alluka.

297
00:19:31,972 --> 00:19:34,174
I’ll be sure to text you
every once in a while.

298
00:19:34,241 --> 00:19:36,710
Gon: Me, too. Hey, listen.

299
00:19:36,777 --> 00:19:38,846
If anything comes up,
let me know.

300
00:19:38,912 --> 00:19:40,680
I’ll do the same, okay?

301
00:19:40,747 --> 00:19:44,884
Killua: Yeah, I definitely will,
because you owe me a lot.

302
00:19:44,952 --> 00:19:46,153
Gon: Huh?

303
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:48,055
Killua: Say hi
to your dad for me.

304
00:19:48,121 --> 00:19:49,055
Gon: Sure.

305
00:19:49,122 --> 00:19:50,357
Killua: I’d go with you,

306
00:19:50,424 --> 00:19:52,259
but i’ve gotta stay with alluka,

307
00:19:52,326 --> 00:19:55,930
and you two haven’t had
a chance to talk alone.

308
00:19:55,996 --> 00:19:57,097
See you around.

309
00:19:57,164 --> 00:19:58,766
Alluka: I’ll let
my big brother go

310
00:19:58,832 --> 00:20:01,868
real soon, okay, after we
spend some time together,

311
00:20:01,935 --> 00:20:04,070
so play with him again
later, please.

312
00:20:04,137 --> 00:20:05,639
Killua: Wait just a minute!

313
00:20:05,706 --> 00:20:07,708
I don’t need you
planning play dates!

314
00:20:07,774 --> 00:20:09,042
Isn’t she great?

315
00:20:09,109 --> 00:20:11,778
Sorry, but you really
can’t compare to her.

316
00:20:11,845 --> 00:20:13,780
( Gon laughing )

317
00:20:17,317 --> 00:20:18,251
( Grunts )

318
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,854
( Killua grunts )

319
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:34,801
Gon: No matter where we go,

320
00:20:34,868 --> 00:20:37,003
we’re part of the gang,

321
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,205
like kite said!

322
00:20:39,273 --> 00:20:40,641
Killua: Right!

323
00:20:40,707 --> 00:20:42,809
♪

324
00:20:45,879 --> 00:20:47,814
( Singing in Japanese )

